CS 340 Bias in Algorithms

---

This repository is an assignment for Computer Ethics at Western Oregon University. The goal of this assignment is to create a basic html website with content that shows our understanding of the bias in agorithms.

**Criteria For This Assignment:**
> - Your website must have at least at least two headings
> - Your website must have four sentences of content
> - Your website must have a list
> - Your website must have at least two images.  This webpage will not be published so you don't need to worry about copyright issues. Use links to external websites for this; a good source is Wikipedia. Example: <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/39/Internet_Key_Layers.png/250px-Internet_Key_Layers.png"></img>
> - Your website must have at least one link
> - Your website must have color 
> - Your website must utilize and cite at least two sources from the week’s read/watch/listen sources.  You can include these citations on the website itself or you can include in a separate bibliography.  
> - Get creative and have fun - be clever, use metaphor, use pictures, use color and other design attributes.
> 
> Western Oregon University-CS 340, Omlid, A. (2026, May 25).

